### Banned (token-heavy — do not select)
- GPT-5.6 Sol, GPT-5.6 Luna, GPT-5.6 Terra, GPT-5.5, GPT-4o in Cursor picker

## Two-Pillar Foundation

### Pillar 1 — CHEAP WORKHORSE (do the work)
Haiku 4.5, Gemini Flash, Grok, DeepSeek via Cursor model picker.
- Cmd+K + Haiku 4.5 for 70%+ of code changes
- Flash/Grok for boilerplate and config
- BugBot for debugging
- Never use Fable/Opus 4.8/Sonnet for inline edits

### Pillar 2 — HIGH-END ARCHITECT (think and decide)
Opus 4.8, Fable 5, Sonnet 5 via Cursor model picker.
- PLAN: schema, ISC, file structure (Opus 4.8 or Fable 5)
- DECIDE: architecture forks, security, cut/continue (Opus 4.8 or Fable 5)
- UI/VOICE/AGENT DESIGN: Sonnet 5 (not GPT Sol)
- VERIFY: ISC check before ship (Sonnet 5)
- LONG CONTEXT: Gemini 3.1 Pro only when reading 100K+ docs
- Never use Haiku for architecture decisions

## Task → Cursor Pro Model Map (No GPT)

| Phase | Select in Cursor | Pillar |
|-------|------------------|--------|
| Architect plan | Opus 4.8 (Fable 5 if complex) | High-end |
| UI / voice / agent design | Sonnet 5 | High-end |
| Fork decision / security | Opus 4.8 or Fable 5 | High-end |
| Multi-file scaffold | Composer (Auto mode) | Built-in |
| Implement features | Haiku 4.5 | Workhorse |
| Inline edits | Cmd+K + Haiku 4.5 | Workhorse |
| Boilerplate | Gemini Flash or Grok 4.5 | Workhorse |
| ISC verify | Sonnet 5 | High-end |
| Long doc read | Gemini 3.1 Pro | High-end |
| Debug | BugBot | Workhorse |
| Unsure | Auto mode (watch it doesn't pick GPT) | Built-in |

## Per-MVP Budget (within A$20/mo pool)

| Phase | Cursor Pro Model | Calls | ~Tokens |
|-------|------------------|-------|---------|
| Plan + architect | Opus 4.8 / Fable 5 | 1-2 | 5-10K |
| Feature / UI design | Sonnet 5 | 3-8 | 10-20K |
| Scaffold | Composer (Auto) | 1-2 | 5-10K |
| Build + edits | Haiku Cmd+K + Flash/Grok | 30-60 | 10-25K |
| Verify | Sonnet 5 | 1-3 | 2-5K |

5-10% high-end calls. 60-70% workhorse calls. Zero GPT.

## Token Rules
- **Never select GPT models in Cursor picker** — biggest token drain
- Select model per phase — don't leave on Sonnet while doing Cmd+K
- High-end for thinking. Workhorse for doing.
- Cmd+K + Haiku = no chat context cost
- @ mention 2-3 files max
- 7-day cut rule on failing bets

## Build Loop
1. PLAN — Opus 4.8 / Fable 5
2. SCAFFOLD — Composer Auto
3. BUILD — Haiku 4.5 Cmd+K + Flash/Grok
4. DECIDE — Opus 4.8 if blocked
5. TEST — no AI
6. VERIFY — Sonnet 5
7. FINALIZE — document, cut or continue

## Stack Defaults (product infra, separate from Cursor Pro)
- Next.js 14+, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Supabase, Stripe, Vercel
- AU dates DD/MM/YYYY, currency AUD, timezone Australia/Sydney

## Portfolio Rules
- 50-55 bets, 1-2 winners expected (2.5% rule)
- 7-day cut rule | Friday review | Document in /reports/
